int main()
{
    int n;
    printf("enter the value of n");
    scanf("%d",&n);
    printf("the number is %d",n);
    return 0;
}

what is a variable?
a variable ia a name in which we assign a value and it is refered to some location in memory.

what is & operator?
it is the address of variable.

what is %d?
%d is an identifier which is used in prinf and scanf.

what is compilation of program means?
it converts high level language to machine level language.

what is meant by running a program?
it means to excitute the code which is written.
